{{Infobox protected area | name = Manglot Wildlife Park | photo = | photo_caption = | photo_width = | location = [[Nizampur, Khyber Pakhtunkhwa|Nizampur]], [[Nowshera district|Nowshera]], [[Khyber Pakhtunkhwa]], [[Pakistan]] | map = | map_caption = | coordinates = | established = {{Start date and years ago|df=yes|mf=no|1990}} | area_acre = 1,756 | area_ref = <ref name="acres">{{cite web|url=http://wildlife.com.pk/conservation/sanctuaries/manglot-wildlife-sanctuary/|publisher=wildlife.com.pk|title=Manglot Wildlife Sanctuary}}</ref> | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | visitation_ref = | governing_body = | website = }}
'''Manglot Wildlife Park''' was established in 1990 in [[Khyber Pakhtunkhwa]], Pakistan; the park is provide a natural sanctuary for wildlife.<ref name="acres"/> The area of the park is spread over on 1,756 acres including hilltops and plain area near the [[Indus River]] in [[Nizampur, Khyber Pakhtunkhwa|Nizampur]], [[Nowshera district|Nowshera]].<ref name="Manglot Wildlife Park">{{cite web|url=https://www.thenews.com.pk/archive/print/219397-manglot-wildlife-park|publisher=thenews.com.pk|title=Manglot Wildlife Park}}</ref><ref name="No to zoos: Animal rights activists press govt for wildlife park">{{cite web|url=http://tribune.com.pk/story/1047545/no-to-zoos-animal-rights-activists-press-govt-for-wildlife-park/|publisher=tribune.com.pk|title=Animal rights activists press govt for wildlife park}}</ref>
==Flora== The flora of the Manglot Wildlife Park include scrub forest primarily consisting of the olive trees. Acacia modesta, zizyphus nummelaria, olea cuspidate, deodonia viscose and monothica boxifolia are the predominantly Vegetation of this park.<ref name="Manglot Wildlife Park, Nizampur">{{cite web|url=http://www.nowshera.org/manglot-wildlife-park-nizampur/|publisher=nowshera.org|title=Manglot Wildlife Park, Nizampur}}</ref>
==Fauna== ===Animals=== The animals includes the Chinkara,<ref name="Return-chinkara">{{cite web|url=http://gupshup.org/gs/science-and-nature/550211-return-chinkara.html|publisher=gupshup.org|title=Return-chinkara}}</ref> hog deer, common leopard, wolf, wild boar, jackal, porcupine and hare.<ref name="Manglot Wildlife Park, Nizampur"/>
===Reptiles=== Including different sort of snakes and wild lizards are present in the park.<ref name="Manglot Wildlife Park, Nizampur"/>
===Birds=== Including Chukar, three varieties of partridges, rock pigeon, dove and several sparrows from different species.<ref name="Manglot Wildlife Park, Nizampur"/>
