{{short description|A group of submerged mountains off the coast of Madagascar}} {{Infobox Seamount | Name = Natal Seamount | Depth = {{convert|18|m|ft|abbr=on|0}} | Height = {{convert|4750|m|ft|abbr=on|-1}} | Map = | Map caption = | Photo = | Photo alt = | Photo caption = | Photo size = | Summit area = | Translation = | Language = | Pronunciation = | Location = | Group = | Coordinates = {{coord|33|12|S|43|50|E}} | Country = | Type = | Volcanic group = | Range = Walters Shoals | Age = | Last activity = | Last eruption = | Discovered = | Discovered by = | First visit = }} The '''Walters Shoals''' is a group of [[Seamount|submerged mountains]] off the coast of [[Madagascar]]. Despite being {{convert|700|km|abbr=out}} from the coast, the tips of some of the mountains are only {{convert|18|m|abbr=out}} below the surface. The Walters Shoals is home to many species of fish, crustaceans, and mollusks. It was discovered in 1963 by the South African Hydrographic Frigate [[HMSAS Natal (K10)|SAS ''Natal'']] captained by [[Johan Charl Walters|Cmdr Walters]]. When found it had a huge population of [[Galápagos shark]]s but they have since been fished out.
